                            <comment id="486917" author="adilger" created="Sat, 7 Feb 2026 23:47:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Use &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19774&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_428: crash on aarch64 - invoked oom-killer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19774&quot;&gt;LU-19774&lt;/a&gt; for tracking the fixing of this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="486915" author="adilger" created="Sat, 7 Feb 2026 23:45:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/63451&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/63451&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18448&quot; title=&quot;Read Directory page on open.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18448&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18448&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: disable dir read on open by default&quot;) landed this issue has been avoided.  Shaun Tancheff has patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/63437&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/63437&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19774&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_428: crash on aarch64 - invoked oom-killer&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19774&quot;&gt;LU-19774&lt;/a&gt; llite: limit dir_read_on_open for non-4k clients&quot;) to further limit this to only clients with large PAGE_SIZE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="485055" author="adilger" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2026 19:39:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still a few being hit, but I think most patches have been rebased to either avoid the last &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18448&quot; title=&quot;Read Directory page on open.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18448&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18448&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; patch landed, on the revert patch, or on the disable patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can search in Maloo for failures, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=green&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;green&quot;&gt;green&lt;/a&gt; would need to give you access to any crash dumps collected by Autotest. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=518400&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=TIMEOUT&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=e3dfa9fe-702c-11e6-8a8c-5254006e85c2&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=518400&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=TIMEOUT&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=e3dfa9fe-702c-11e6-8a8c-5254006e85c2&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="485008" author="shadow" created="Thu, 22 Jan 2026 16:30:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;is any new OOM hits?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="484282" author="adilger" created="Fri, 16 Jan 2026 23:21:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patches that are hitting this failure cannot pass by retesting, and must be rebased to get a fix.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please use commit 815dfd3451 if your patch is isolated and can rebase cleanly from the tip of master to that commit (i.e. does not have any conflicts with patches landed since then).  If that is not possible, try to rebase (but do not modify) onto the patch that is reverting the broken fix with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;git fetch ssh://review.whamcloud.com:29418/fs/lustre-release refs/changes/66/63366/2 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; git checkout FETCH_HEAD&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (or your equivalent from the &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&#10247;-&amp;gt; Download patch- &amp;gt; Checkout&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; menu item on &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/63366&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;patch 63366&lt;/a&gt;.  &lt;b&gt;DO NOT&lt;/b&gt; rebase or modify that patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hopefully that patch will land quickly and this issue will be behind us.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483595" author="adilger" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2026 07:19:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Arshad Hussain &amp;lt;arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63366&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/63366&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: Revert &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18448&quot; title=&quot;Read Directory page on open.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18448&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18448&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: read dir on open fixes&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 0d30d882a213c4c29ffe21e0218d6570fb66a0af&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483587" author="adilger" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2026 06:31:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/61641&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/61641&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18448&quot; title=&quot;Read Directory page on open.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18448&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18448&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; llite: read dir on open fixes&quot;) is very likely the cause of the aarch64 failures.  3/3 patches based on that patch have failed on aarch64, while 5/5 patches based on the previous patch have passed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483559" author="adilger" created="Mon, 12 Jan 2026 22:44:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is looking like &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18448&quot; title=&quot;Read Directory page on open.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18448&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18448&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; may be the source of the aarch64+64k issues.  Patches that were rebased to intermediate offsets have continued to see timeouts in test_398b, test_421, or OOM crashes in test_428.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve rebased a number of the failing patches onto commit 815dfd3451 (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19750&quot; title=&quot;interop: master+b2_15 client can&amp;#39;t access changelog due to missing mdt_body in open request&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19750&quot;&gt;LU-19750&lt;/a&gt; ptlrpc: llog client to set mdt_body&quot;) to see if they will now pass, as this is the earliest patch after 2.17.50 that can possibly work (due to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19750&quot; title=&quot;interop: master+b2_15 client can&amp;#39;t access changelog due to missing mdt_body in open request&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19750&quot;&gt;LU-19750&lt;/a&gt; causing widespread llog &quot;interop&quot; failures and needing that patch to fix the issues).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="483397" author="adilger" created="Sun, 11 Jan 2026 20:52:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is being hit almost exclusively on master aarch64 el9.5 clients, with one hit during interop testing with a b2_15 x86 server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this may be a fairly persistent error, one trivial (comment-only) patch I saw failed on two retries. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This looks like it was introduced on 2026-01-08:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=2332800&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=TIMEOUT&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=e3dfa9fe-702c-11e6-8a8c-5254006e85c2&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=2332800&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=TIMEOUT&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=e3dfa9fe-702c-11e6-8a8c-5254006e85c2&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patches landed on 2026-01-07:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
